  "text": "SonarSnoop can be extended to use additional sensor inputs to boost performance. The combination of multiple sensing inputs has been used successfully in the past. For instance, Simon et al. make use of the front phone camera and microphone recording to infer personal identification numbers (PINs) [CITATION_1] . They use the front camera to record a video when people input, by tapping on the screen, PINs. The recorded acoustic signal helps to identify frames in which a PIN is entered. Machine learning is used to identify the pressed number in the identified frames. Narain et al. combine a gyroscope and microphone to unveil PINs [CITATION_2] . Sound and gyroscopes data are used to detect finger tap location on the virtual keyboard or PIN pad.",
